turn out to be particularly useful in\nthe present article.\n  Finally, for general matrix codes, we prove that the equivalence problem\n(both left and right) is at least as hard as the well--studied {\\em Monomial\nEquivalence Problem} for codes endowed with the Hamming metric.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 9 Nov 2020 18:14:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 10 Jun 2021 13:38:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-11"}
