 the\nexperimental result, although we slightly overestimate the data around the\nlow-energy peak of the $dB(E1)/d\\varepsilon$ distribution. Finally, we show\nthat a reduction of the $n$-$n$ interaction range produces a significant\nreduction of the $s$-wave contribution, which then should be expected in\ncalculations using contact interactions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 10 Nov 2020 09:24:39 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 1 Dec 2020 10:38:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-12-02"}
